Normally, it would not have been a problem to wait that long to place our order but we were literally the ONLY table in the whole place. I had to go up to the bar to get our waitress to take our order. Then when our food was served the plates were SO hot the waitress had oven mitts on to serve us. I work down the street and decided to meet my mother for lunch.   I am so glad I did.  The food was fresh (it did take a bit of time for it to get to us but that is because everything was MADE TO ORDER) and this is NOT taco bell or chipotle. I am a vegan and I ordered the Veggie Burrito minus the cheese and my mother had the beef fajitas.  First off, the portions are HUGE.  I joked that I didn't get a burrito but an arm.  It was two meals for me, and at that price, that is pretty amazing.  While we waited, we were given a basket of warm salty thin crispy tortilla chips.  YUM!  I find it fairly easy to go to most restaurants as a Vegan and this one was no exception.  In fact, once they found out I was a vegan they started telling me about items that they have that aren't on the menu YET that I could order next time. And there WILL be a next time.  We sat at the bar (it's a tiny place and packed when we went) and the girls serving us were just so kind and wonderful. And they do TACO TUESDAYS!!  Recommend to anyone!!!
